    <p>You should tell users if:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>they have included letters</li>
        <li>they have submitted a number that is too short or too long (not including spaces)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You should check:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>check if the user has submitted a National Insurance number and advise the user if they have</li>
        <li>check their NHS number is valid against a modulus 11 algorithm</li>
    </ul>



    <h2>Research</h2>
    <p>Research from the National Data Opt-out Programme showed that:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>patients did not always know what their NHS number looked like</li>
        <li>patients did not know where they could find their NHS number</li>
        <li>some patients thought they were being asked for their National Insurance number</li>
        <li>telling patients where to find their NHS number before and after starting the service was more effective for users</li>
    </ul>


